review_blob: I have been enjoying this hoppy imperial stout.. I look forward to cracking one open after a long night of work, put my feet up, and watch the late night shows.. a bit high in ABV with 9% but still enjoy to the last drop
Can taste the coffee and chocolate, a nice roasty porter... I am a big fan of Great Lakes.. never met a Great Lakes that I didnt like
This one has a nice amber color through the glass.. slight caramel flavor with a white head.  Nothing too special here to report on
A good raspberry wheat beer... I would only drink one of these however... very fruity with a faded purple color to it.  Enjoyable wheat beer
An appealing amber appearance... not so hot on the initial taste... but after a few sips... this amber ale becomes soothing.  Good size head that lasts after the pour
This is only the second style of Sierra Nevada that I have had.. but I did enjoy this porter... with a roasted barley and rich, smooth flavor
Another decent beer from Victory Brewing.. subtle aroma and flavor.. golden in color
A great dark pale ale... no head on the pour.. chocolate malt with a very dark amber in color
This light ale has a great taste when served with a lemon wedge. A hazy yellow appearance with a nice head. I enjoyed this wheat and will have it again for sure.
Im trying to drink all of the Liberty brews, the raspberry wheat is one of my favorite.  A nice berry aroma, with a subtle berry taste but not too overwhelming which is what I liked.
I enjoyed this summer ale, always a big fan of a summer brew. nice crisp refreshing taste with a hint of citrusy aroma and taste.
A great dark ale, chocolate malt taste, very smooth and full bodied, would get this again for sure
beer_name: Liberty Myrtle Beach Nut Brown Ale

review_blob: Nice dark red ale, trying to try all the Liberty beers, one of the best ales that I have had
beer_name: Liberty Myrtle Beach Rockets Red Ale

review_blob: Just randomly chose this beer from Beijing off of the shelf... nothing too special here, just your typical pale lager...
A nice belgian-style wheat beer... a hazy yellow in appearance... soft aromas and a good beer from Michigan Brewing
very deep ruby color.... light dark head. nice dark appearance, this is the first doppelbock that i have had..... not too shabby
cloudy yellow brew...... decent pilsner, very smooth... light head. Hoppy aroma
This one is very hoppy, crisp sunshine taste to it... great german style pilsner to relax to
Nice golden appearance, crisp taste, soothing aftertaste all the way through the bottle
Nothing too special with this Pittsburgh brew... golden amber color, lighter flavor
Subtle spice aroma, copper with tan head that likes to hang around,  I actually liked this one.. it is always nice to support the local Pennsylvanian breweries
cloudy amber appearance, aroma wasnt the best... after the first sip, this lager does get better however, very smooth.... just wanted to try something new
Tasteful blueberry ale, strong aroma with subtle blueberry flavor, just the right amount
Had this in a pint bottle, enjoyed it very much, hint of hops but balanced very well as you drink
Very flavorful with hint of fruit and spice together, another great one from Great Lakes, gotta hand it to Cleveland
beer_name: Great Lakes Holy Moses White Ale

review_blob: Very nice ale to sit back during the winter and sip on this one, very relaxing and warming, happy with this winter ale
beer_name: Southern Tier Old Man Winter Ale

review_blob: I couldnt beleive how strong this one was with 9% alcohol volume, a few of these and you are feeling it... nice belgian style beer
I loved this one by Southern Tier, the aroma and taste was extraordinary, phin and matt did a great job on this one!
beer_name: Southern Tier PMX (Phin & Matts Extraordinary Ale)

review_blob: This is a great IPA, i really enjoy this style, very aromatic of hops, very fresh taste
I havent had St. Pauli Girl Lager yet, but I enjoyed this nice dark lager, smooth flow and satisfying taste, I enjoy having a dark beer during the winter months, so of course, I enjoyed this
Another beer that I wasnt too sure about with the spice and ginger flavor, but yet I wasnt appalled by it either, Great Lakes puts out a huge variety, and I am always willing to try a new one
I really enjoy Erdinger, dont have the chance to drink it all too often, nice golden appearance, enjoyable aroma and taste

A dark brew from Pottsville, didnt entirely enjoy the palate, but one of those beers that gets better as you drink, a nice porter to relax to in the winter, cant talk trash on this because of my love for Yuengling
Nice dark amber appearance, soothing taste, but nothing too special here, had this out of an ale and lager variety pack, aroma is pleasing

Well, knowing that this had some spice to it, I wasnt too enthused, but I wanted to try it anyway, the initial taste I didnt like, but then after the first couple sips it got better, dark appearance, aroma of pumpkin and spice
I didnt enjoy the initial taste, but then it grew on me after a few more sips... i would say it is worth the money, it is overall a good wheat beer
This is a great fall beer, perfect for the season, golden appearance, can pick up on the sweet flavors
UPDATED: SEP 23, 2005
Had this in the can, the only good that can come out of this beer is its high alcohol content, taste is horrible, aroma even worse
Bought a couple of forties of Old German... well what can you really say about this one, its CHEAP, that is about it

We have this on tap at work, to tell you the truth, you dont feel like your drinking a beer, it is however, refreshing, strong strawberry taste and goes down smooth, this is fine to have one pint but no more than that
Had this one in Windsor, first Polish beer that I think I have had, nothing outstanding but overall appealling, should have bought another to get a true sense for it
A nice cider, yellowish gold colour, overall a decent cider, sweet taste, plus... you have to love the name of it
This cider has a cloudy appearance, very tasty, now that I have been trying a lot of ciders, I am getting an idea of what is a good cider and what is not
I finally tried Leffe, blond beer with a dark appearance, I agree that it is a connoisseur beer, most people probably would not enjoy but I did
Pours a dark amber, the bartender convinced me to try this, enjoyable bitter, but nothing stands out in this one

beer_brewer_name: Magners GB / Shepton Mallet Cider Mill (C&C; Group)
review_blob: I thought this was a decent cider, had this at The Setting Sun Pub, a cloudy appearance, had a different bite to it compared to other ciders I have had
Doesnt beat Westons Organic Cider, but is tasty, a medium dry cider, quenches your thirst, sweet aroma , nice appearance
beer_name: Westons Stowford Press Medium Dry Cider

review_blob: I really enjoyed this cider, 6.5% alcohol which is incredible, it only takes a couple of these to feel pretty good, I was impressed by this, a bit expensive, but worth the money for sure
A decent cider, saw commercials all over the tv and they have it on tap everywhere, your typical cider, nothing special here
